The main commands of frame technology
- invoke a frame (a procedure call that occurs at construction time, while constructing program texts);
-- "call"/"run" an assembly
--- managed by basii paragraph management
-- input management

- assign a (list of) expression(s) to a frame parameter (a construction-time variable assignment);
-- better to use arrays of variables.
-- let var{[expression]} = expression?

- insert frame-text 
-- before, instead-of, or after blocks of frame-text (ie markers), 
--- (OR beginning of file, or append to file?) 
-labeled by parameter expressions;
- instantiate a frame parameter (a construction-time expression evaluation);
-- apply an assembly to a frame/template
--- all var markers will be replaced
- select frame-texts for processing (a construction-time case statement);
-- where is this different from instantiate a frame parameter?
- iterate a frame-text while varying certain frame parameters (a construction-time while statement).
-- more like a FOR loop

- output management
-- set output filename
-- output frame to file
